    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Replace magic number 0 with symbolic constant in NR TLV unpacking functions\n\n### Summary\nIn the NR P7 message unpacking functions, a magic number 0 was being used when calling `unpack_nr_p7_tlv_list` for messages with no TLV elements. This made the code less readable and harder to maintain.\n\nThis fix introduces a symbolic constant `NFAPI_NR_P7_TLV_LIST_EMPTY` to clearly indicate the intent of an empty TLV list.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/nfapi/public_inc/nfapi_nr_interface_scf.h`: Added `NFAPI_NR_P7_TLV_LIST_EMPTY` constant\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/nfapi/src/nfapi_p7.c`: Updated three NR functions to use the new constant:\n  - `unpack_nr_dl_node_sync` \n  - `unpack_nr_ul_node_sync`\n  - `unpack_nr_timing_info`\n\n### Reproduction\nWithout this fix, code reviewers and maintainers need to understand that the magic number 0 in the context of `unpack_nr_p7_tlv_list` means \"empty TLV list\". This can lead to confusion when maintaining or extending these functions. The symbolic constant makes the intent explicit and improves code clarity.\n"
}